│ Def by falling through the code path that sets an insertion point after       │
│ LastInst, regardless of whether we will later just broadcast.                 │
│                                                                               │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                       │
│ - In VPTransformState::get(const VPValue*, bool NeedsScalar), when            │
│ NeedsScalar is false and we need a vector value, we build it from existing    │
│ scalar values:                                                                │
│   - We determine if Def is uniform after vectorization. If uniform, we will   │
│ broadcast the scalar using GetBroadcastInstrs, which hoists the broadcast     │
│ into the vector preheader.                                                    │
│   - However, before that branch we unconditionally compute LastInst and set   │
│ the IRBuilder insertion point to the instruction after LastInst (or after     │
│ last PHI if LastInst is a PHI). If LastInst is an invoke (a terminator) in    │
│ its block, std::next(iterator(LastInst)) is end(), and dereferencing it       │
│ triggers the assertion.                                                       │
│ - In this reproducer, Def is the VPExpandSCEV of %step, which resolves to the │
│ invoke instruction in entry. LastInst is that invoke. Attempting to set the   │
│ insertion point after it dereferences the end sentinel and aborts.            │
│ - The code also does not need to touch the insertion point at all for the     │
│ uniform path, since GetBroadcastInstrs has its own InsertPointGuard and       │
│ hoists into the vector preheader when safe.                                   │
│                                                                               │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                                    │
│ - File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlan.cpp, lines 321-351 in             │
│ VPTransformState::get(const VPValue*, bool).                                  │
│ - Change: Only compute and set the insertion point for the non-uniform case.  │
│ For the uniform case, broadcast directly and return, avoiding any attempt to  │
│ advance past a possible terminator. Additionally, when computing the          │
│ insertion point for non-uniform values, handle the case where LastInst is a   │
│ terminator by inserting before it (use getNextNode() and fall back to         │
│ LastInst if null) instead of dereferencing end().                             │
│                                                                               │
│ Proposed replacement for lines 321-351:                                       │
│                                                                               │
│   Value *VectorValue = nullptr;                                               │
│   if (IsUniform) {                                                            │
│     VectorValue = GetBroadcastInstrs(ScalarValue);                            │
│     set(Def, VectorValue);                                                    │
│     return VectorValue;                                                       │
│   }                                                                           │
│                                                                               │
│   // For non-uniform values, construct the vector by packing scalar lanes.    │
│   // Set the insert point after the last scalarized instruction or after the  │
│   // last PHI, if LastInst is a PHI. If LastInst is a terminator, insert      │
│ before                                                                        │
│   // it.                                                                      │
│   auto *LastInst = cast<Instruction>(get(Def, LastLane));                     │
│   auto OldIP = Builder.saveIP();                                              │
│   BasicBlock::iterator NewIP =                                                │
│       isa<PHINode>(LastInst)                                                  │
│           ? LastInst->getParent()->getFirstNonPHIIt()                         │
│           : BasicBlock::iterator(LastInst->getNextNode() ?                    │
│ LastInst->getNextNode()                                                       │
│                                                          : LastInst);         │
│   Builder.SetInsertPoint(&*NewIP);                                            │
│                                                                               │
│   // Initialize packing with insertelements to start from undef.              │
│   assert(!VF.isScalable() && "VF is assumed to be non scalable.");            │
│   Value *Undef = PoisonValue::get(toVectorizedTy(LastInst->getType(), VF));   │
│   set(Def, Undef);                                                            │
│   for (unsigned Lane = 0; Lane < VF.getKnownMinValue(); ++Lane)               │
│     packScalarIntoVectorizedValue(Def, Lane);                                 │
│   VectorValue = get(Def);                                                     │
│   Builder.restoreIP(OldIP);                                                   │
│   return VectorValue;                                                         │
│                                                                               │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                │
│ - The crash was caused by dereferencing a BasicBlock end iterator when trying │
│ to insert “after” a terminator instruction (invoke). By deferring             │
│ insertion-point manipulation to only the non-uniform case and guarding        │
│ against terminators by inserting before them, we avoid the invalid iterator   │
│ dereference. For uniform values, we now rely solely on GetBroadcastInstrs to  │
│ hoist broadcasts safely. This fixes the assertion while preserving the        │
│ intended insertion positions and behavior.                                    │
